pulfalight.title: Evaluate and ensure that Aeon Activity support is integrated with request functionality

comments.body: @jrgriffiniii I think this is something we will have to test out with the External Requests approach we are currently taking and see if we might be able to map a value to [the "Request For" field](https://support.atlas-sys.com/hc/en-us/articles/360011819214-Submitting-Requests-for-Activities). Good news is that Aeon [plans on releasing enhancements for both the API and Requests from External Systems in Q3 of this year](https://support.atlas-sys.com/hc/en-us/articles/360011819214-Submitting-Requests-for-Activities).

It looks like we can supply the `ForActivity` field when Requests are submitted. The Activity must already have been created in Aeon and we need to send the ActivityID. See the _Special Request Parameters_ section on the [External Requests Documentation Page](https://support.atlas-sys.com/hc/en-us/articles/360011820054-External-Request-Endpoint).
